1
00:00:01,150 --> 00:00:03,170
I'm Kakeru.

2
00:00:05,060 --> 00:00:07,710
Kakeru?

3
00:00:13,670 --> 00:00:17,010
Have we met somewhere before?

4
00:00:17,930 --> 00:00:19,330
Huh?

5
00:00:23,757 --> 00:00:26,677
It's Kakeru. Kakeru Sorano.

6
00:00:26,677 --> 00:00:30,397
Ushio said he saw you
going into the hospital.

7
00:00:32,650 --> 00:00:34,160
So you must be surprised by my visit.

8
00:00:34,870 --> 00:00:37,210
you must be surprised by my visit.

9
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:43,610
I'm sorry,

10
00:00:44,740 --> 00:00:46,320
but I don't know you.

11
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:49,000
- Kakeru.
- Kakeru.

12
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,615
Oh, Koharu!

13
00:00:50,615 --> 00:00:54,305
Thank goodness! We were so worried.

14
00:00:55,615 --> 00:00:57,890
Sorry for barging in like this.

15
00:00:57,890 --> 00:01:01,450
We got worried
since you've been missing class.

16
00:01:01,450 --> 00:01:03,250
Are you not feeling well?

17
00:01:06,310 --> 00:01:07,570
What's wrong?

18
00:01:08,825 --> 00:01:11,100
Who are you people?

19
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:11,875
Huh?

20
00:01:11,875 --> 00:01:14,165
Who are you?

21
00:01:14,165 --> 00:01:15,030
It's Yuuko.

22
00:01:15,030 --> 00:01:17,285
Don't touch me!

23
00:01:17,285 --> 00:01:19,045
I'll call for help!

24
00:01:22,195 --> 00:01:23,900
Koharu.

25
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,230
Mom.

26
00:01:25,230 --> 00:01:27,152
Go back to your room.

27
00:01:27,152 --> 00:01:30,402
Ms. Fuyutsuki,
I'll take your white cane for now.

28
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:36,460
Hold onto me. Let's go.

29
00:01:39,615 --> 00:01:41,220
Thank you.

30
00:01:41,220 --> 00:01:43,955
Watch your step, please.

31
00:01:43,955 --> 00:01:45,185
Let's go.

32
00:01:53,285 --> 00:01:57,960
So, Koharu really doesn't remember us?

33
00:01:57,960 --> 00:02:02,770
Apparently, the medication
can sometimes cloud her memory.

34
00:02:03,535 --> 00:02:08,100
This level of severity is rare,
but the doctor says it's not unheard of.

35
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:10,370
Is Koharu not feeling well?

36
00:02:11,875 --> 00:02:14,610
She's staying here for a while,

37
00:02:14,610 --> 00:02:18,180
but she's doing her best
to show you her lively self again.

38
00:02:20,930 --> 00:02:22,920
Sorry for worrying you.

39
00:02:23,745 --> 00:02:27,380
But for now, can you give her some space?

40
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:29,760
Bye then.

41
00:02:32,540 --> 00:02:33,820
When...

42
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:40,110
When do her memories stop?

43
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:49,200
If there really is a god,

44
00:02:51,230 --> 00:02:53,340
I bet he's a real jerk.

45
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,350
Yeah.

46
00:02:58,935 --> 00:03:03,300
Koharu graduated from high school
while she was blind,

47
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:04,830
and got into college.

48
00:03:06,325 --> 00:03:11,680
I can't even imagine
how hard that must have been.

49
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:15,170
But she doesn't remember
all that hard work, does she?

50
00:03:17,781 --> 00:03:20,641
Well, she forgot the last one to two years.

51
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:24,020
Yeah.

52
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:26,690
That's too cruel.

53
00:03:28,055 --> 00:03:32,680
But still, her mom said
it's a side effect from her meds,

54
00:03:33,610 --> 00:03:35,070
so when that's over...

55
00:03:36,377 --> 00:03:38,717
Maybe it's just temporary, right?

56
00:03:41,307 --> 00:03:42,380
But...

57
00:03:43,236 --> 00:03:45,346
what if she never remembers?

58
00:03:48,326 --> 00:03:54,496
Does that mean all the time
we spent together is gone?

59
00:03:58,830 --> 00:04:00,080
You okay?

60
00:04:05,306 --> 00:04:07,396
How could I be okay?

61
00:04:11,430 --> 00:04:12,540
But...

62
00:04:14,836 --> 00:04:17,666
Koharu's probably struggling the most.

63
00:04:28,246 --> 00:04:31,086
Are you sure this is what you want?

64
00:04:37,267 --> 00:04:39,297
I'll head out for today then.

65
00:04:40,364 --> 00:04:42,329
- Okay.
- Okay.

66
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:42,190
[Episode 5]

67
00:05:43,990 --> 00:05:46,130
Koharu, your lunch.

68
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:48,390
Is something wrong?

69
00:05:52,540 --> 00:05:53,660
My eyes...

70
00:05:59,565 --> 00:06:02,420
Intraocular lymphoma?

71
00:06:02,420 --> 00:06:04,936
To put it simply,

72
00:06:04,936 --> 00:06:07,116
it's cancer inside the eye.

73
00:06:10,825 --> 00:06:12,140
If left untreated,

74
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:15,440
it's a disease
that is likely to spread elsewhere.

75
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:19,105
However, if we start chemotherapy
from this stage,

76
00:06:19,105 --> 00:06:21,155
it shouldn't be life-threatening.

77
00:06:23,420 --> 00:06:24,420
And my eyes?

78
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:30,050
When I'm better,
I can see normally again, right?

79
00:06:38,085 --> 00:06:39,510
Koharu, stop!

80
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:41,140
Let go of me!

81
00:06:43,955 --> 00:06:46,230
Didn't you hear the doctor?

82
00:06:46,230 --> 00:06:48,245
If we cure it quickly, your eyes can...

83
00:06:48,245 --> 00:06:49,985
There's no point!

84
00:06:51,230 --> 00:06:53,640
My sight is fading more and more.

85
00:07:01,030 --> 00:07:02,180
I...

86
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:08,905
can't even see your face
clearly anymore, Mom.

87
00:07:11,866 --> 00:07:13,176
It's okay.

88
00:07:15,194 --> 00:07:18,436
Everything will be okay.
It's okay, it's okay.

89
00:07:25,395 --> 00:07:26,690
Thank you for your help.

90
00:07:26,690 --> 00:07:28,110
Take care.

91
00:07:28,950 --> 00:07:30,540
Thank you.

92
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:38,410
I can't even sense light anymore.

93
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,440
Huh?

94
00:07:42,540 --> 00:07:45,110
It's all invisible now.

95
00:07:45,110 --> 00:07:47,060
The things in front of me.

96
00:08:00,235 --> 00:08:04,710
<i>Even after losing my sight,
I could still walk.</i>

97
00:08:06,830 --> 00:08:08,310
<i>But...</i>

98
00:08:09,410 --> 00:08:14,220
<i>I didn't know what direction to live for.</i>

99
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,350
Fireworks...

100
00:08:41,130 --> 00:08:43,090
<i>In this invisible world,</i>

101
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:46,000
<i>I...</i>

102
00:08:48,180 --> 00:08:49,690
<i>was still alive.</i>

103
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:10,710
<i>I decided to live in this world
with all my might.</i>

104
00:09:13,430 --> 00:09:17,860
<i>I decided to do everything I wanted.</i>

105
00:09:20,065 --> 00:09:22,110
I'm Kakeru.

106
00:09:22,110 --> 00:09:23,540
Kakeru.

107
00:09:24,185 --> 00:09:26,260
Can you read braille?

108
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:29,615
No, I just remember the line.

109
00:09:29,615 --> 00:09:32,215
You must really love it!

110
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:44,120
<i>I never...</i>

111
00:09:45,252 --> 00:09:50,616
<i>I never even imagined
that a day would come...</i>

112
00:09:50,616 --> 00:09:52,436
<i>when I could laugh like this.</i>

113
00:10:04,479 --> 00:10:06,340
Koharu.

114
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:09,362
Koharu!

115
00:10:13,020 --> 00:10:14,170
Koharu.

116
00:10:16,260 --> 00:10:17,480
It's Miura.

117
00:10:19,550 --> 00:10:23,280
Can we talk for a bit?

118
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,910
The lymphoma has relapsed.

119
00:10:38,140 --> 00:10:39,450
Your chances...

120
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:48,390
<i>I felt more despair
than when I lost my sight.</i>

121
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:52,710
<i>I never could've imagined...</i>

122
00:10:57,605 --> 00:11:00,600
Can I take a video?

123
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,025
Huh, why?

124
00:11:02,025 --> 00:11:04,855
I want to capture bits of my daily life.

125
00:11:07,305 --> 00:11:09,450
Even if I can't see,

126
00:11:09,450 --> 00:11:14,562
hearing your voice or sounds from that moment

127
00:11:14,562 --> 00:11:16,311
can remind me of those times.

128
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:19,980
Sorry to keep you waiting!
Are you ready?

129
00:11:19,980 --> 00:11:21,050
Yeah.

130
00:11:21,050 --> 00:11:22,170
Yuuko?

131
00:11:22,170 --> 00:11:24,760
Yeah, I have to go, too.

132
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:26,200
I see.

133
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,651
I'll be off then.

134
00:11:27,651 --> 00:11:30,231
See you later, Koharu.

135
00:11:32,715 --> 00:11:34,900
I'll walk you to the gate.

136
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:35,870
Are you sure?

137
00:11:35,870 --> 00:11:38,315
Why not? It's fine!

138
00:11:38,315 --> 00:11:39,535
See you later.

139
00:11:41,326 --> 00:11:43,436
[Fuyutsuki]
I'm back.

140
00:11:44,545 --> 00:11:46,340
Welcome back.

141
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:48,590
Did you tell everyone?

142
00:11:52,510 --> 00:11:54,430
I said, "See you later."

143
00:11:57,350 --> 00:11:59,430
Even though we might not meet again.

144
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:08,010
<i>You've received a video from Kakeru.</i>

145
00:12:23,046 --> 00:12:26,706
<i>I was scared of feeling happy.</i>

146
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:32,140
<i>Caring deeply for anyone...</i>

147
00:12:34,090 --> 00:12:37,180
<i>or being remembered by people...</i>

148
00:12:39,050 --> 00:12:40,990
<i>I'd avoid it.</i>

149
00:12:42,236 --> 00:12:46,696
<i>Otherwise, it hurts too much
when someone leaves.</i>

150
00:12:47,976 --> 00:12:52,400
<i>But, spending time with you, Koharu...</i>

151
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:54,754
<i>little by little,</i>

152
00:12:54,754 --> 00:12:59,604
<i>my once colorless routine
bloomed with color.</i>

153
00:13:01,147 --> 00:13:05,387
<i>Of course, I still don't know
much about you, Koharu.</i>

154
00:13:07,186 --> 00:13:11,886
<i>There's probably
a lot about you I don't know yet.</i>

155
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:18,010
<i>But I can learn from now on.</i>

156
00:13:19,226 --> 00:13:22,936
<i>I just need to spend more time with you.</i>

157
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:31,950
<i>I won't let the fear of losing someone
hold me back any longer.</i>

158
00:13:33,965 --> 00:13:36,410
<i>The sounds of this town,</i>

159
00:13:36,410 --> 00:13:38,740
<i>the birds chirping,</i>

160
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:40,930
<i>the train running...</i>

161
00:13:42,916 --> 00:13:44,886
<i>With all these sounds,</i>

162
00:13:46,076 --> 00:13:50,576
<i>I want you to hear what I'm about to say.</i>

163
00:13:53,650 --> 00:13:55,000
<i>I like you,</i>

164
00:13:56,150 --> 00:13:57,830
<i>Koharu.</i>

165
00:14:01,735 --> 00:14:06,720
<i>If it's okay, I'd like to be with you
from now on.</i>

166
00:14:31,950 --> 00:14:33,360
What's wrong?

167
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,970
I have a request.

168
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:43,320
When I'm gone,

169
00:14:45,936 --> 00:14:50,276
if that hurts Kakeru...

170
00:14:51,095 --> 00:14:54,790
No. That's the one thing
I absolutely can't bear.

171
00:14:56,450 --> 00:14:57,980
So...

172
00:14:59,947 --> 00:15:02,317
before I disappear...

173
00:15:04,175 --> 00:15:10,130
I want to erase all the time
Kakeru spent with me.

174
00:15:25,740 --> 00:15:27,270
I'm sorry,

175
00:15:29,190 --> 00:15:30,900
Kakeru.

176
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:42,240
It's very popular.

177
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:43,109
Huh?

178
00:15:43,109 --> 00:15:47,940
Your piano performances.
The children love them.

179
00:15:47,940 --> 00:15:49,580
Is that so?

180
00:15:49,580 --> 00:15:50,408
Yeah.

181
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:54,877
Oh, starting today, there's someone new
joining us as a volunteer,

182
00:15:54,877 --> 00:15:56,695
so please treat him well.

183
00:15:56,695 --> 00:15:57,695
Okay.

184
00:15:59,045 --> 00:16:01,740
Oh, this way, please.

185
00:16:01,740 --> 00:16:05,565
Ms. Fuyutsuki, this is the new volunteer.

186
00:16:12,820 --> 00:16:14,190
I'm Kakeru.

187
00:16:20,490 --> 00:16:22,220
Ms. Fuyutsuki?

188
00:16:24,290 --> 00:16:25,290
Oh...

189
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:27,790
I'm Koharu.

190
00:16:29,830 --> 00:16:31,710
Nice to meet you.

191
00:16:39,225 --> 00:16:40,020
Hm?

192
00:16:40,020 --> 00:16:41,765
[Children's Playroom: Volunteers Wanted]

193
00:16:41,765 --> 00:16:43,025
What's this?

194
00:16:45,820 --> 00:16:49,820
I decided to go as a volunteer for a while.

195
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:54,530
If I try to visit normally,
she'd probably say no.

196
00:16:56,915 --> 00:17:00,440
Looks like Koharu
doesn't remember us at all.

197
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:01,640
I know.

198
00:17:02,630 --> 00:17:05,940
But if we're together,
she might remember something.

199
00:17:07,615 --> 00:17:10,060
It's okay if she can't remember.

200
00:17:10,060 --> 00:17:11,190
Huh?

201
00:17:18,360 --> 00:17:21,350
You're the person
who came the other day, right?

202
00:17:24,273 --> 00:17:25,273
Yeah.

203
00:17:28,010 --> 00:17:29,830
Why are you here?

204
00:17:30,466 --> 00:17:35,106
We probably knew each other from before,

205
00:17:35,910 --> 00:17:40,460
but I don't remember anything anymore.

206
00:17:43,710 --> 00:17:44,860
So...

207
00:17:45,930 --> 00:17:47,490
That's fine.

208
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:50,110
Huh?

209
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:52,710
What do you mean?

210
00:17:56,059 --> 00:17:59,019
We can just start over from the beginning.

211
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:10,760
It's already been two weeks
since Kakeru started volunteering.

212
00:18:11,660 --> 00:18:13,510
Have you heard anything?

213
00:18:15,430 --> 00:18:16,980
Not from Kakeru.

214
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:20,240
If he's not saying anything,

215
00:18:21,490 --> 00:18:24,950
Koharu's memory
probably hasn't come back or anything.

216
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:30,220
And yet he still keeps visiting her.

217
00:18:31,675 --> 00:18:37,130
Honestly, I think it's amazing
to care about someone like that.

218
00:18:38,675 --> 00:18:40,270
Yeah.

219
00:18:40,270 --> 00:18:41,500
Oh, I mean...

220
00:18:44,770 --> 00:18:46,010
Well...

221
00:18:47,730 --> 00:18:51,600
I wonder if there's anything we can do, too.

222
00:19:03,395 --> 00:19:05,460
Kakeru!

223
00:19:05,460 --> 00:19:07,120
What? You're heavy!

224
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:08,780
You're too loud.

225
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:11,505
Call him Mr. Sorano, not Kakeru.

226
00:19:11,505 --> 00:19:12,995
Kakeru is fine.

227
00:19:14,029 --> 00:19:17,220
By the way, why are you
always looking at Koharu?

228
00:19:17,220 --> 00:19:18,630
Yeah!

229
00:19:18,630 --> 00:19:19,580
I'm not looking!

230
00:19:19,580 --> 00:19:22,280
You like Koharu, don't you?

231
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:24,560
That's exactly it!

232
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:26,140
Koharu looks so happy!

233
00:19:26,140 --> 00:19:31,800
Oh! Lovebirds!

234
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:34,640
Shut up!

235
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:36,630
Bye, Koharu, Kakeru.

236
00:19:36,630 --> 00:19:37,520
Later.

237
00:19:37,520 --> 00:19:39,555
- Bye, Kakeru.
- Bye.

238
00:19:39,555 --> 00:19:41,685
- Bye-bye!
- Bye-bye!

239
00:19:47,910 --> 00:19:48,910
Well,

240
00:19:49,703 --> 00:19:51,143
later then.

241
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:53,800
Um...

242
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:03,610
Do you have a moment?

243
00:20:14,367 --> 00:20:15,857
It's cold, huh?

244
00:20:16,845 --> 00:20:21,176
Oh, should I get you a warm drink?

245
00:20:21,176 --> 00:20:23,406
Could you please leave me alone?

246
00:20:25,670 --> 00:20:26,980
I feel like...

247
00:20:28,410 --> 00:20:33,220
I won't be able to remember you.

248
00:20:35,696 --> 00:20:39,216
I don't mind if you can't remember.

249
00:20:48,873 --> 00:20:52,530
Losing something
doesn't mean you lose everything.

250
00:20:52,530 --> 00:20:54,670
You told me that.

251
00:20:57,160 --> 00:21:01,850
I'll remember all our time together.

252
00:21:07,170 --> 00:21:08,780
I don't want that.

253
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:12,830
It's better...

254
00:21:14,820 --> 00:21:17,070
if we cut ties.

255
00:21:20,340 --> 00:21:21,780
I only...

256
00:21:24,660 --> 00:21:26,970
have about six months left.

257
00:21:32,090 --> 00:21:35,350
The tumor I had before has come back,

258
00:21:35,350 --> 00:21:40,210
and it seems to have reached
my brain and other organs.

259
00:21:43,370 --> 00:21:44,630
What?

260
00:21:48,684 --> 00:21:50,499
I'm gonna die soon anyway.

261
00:21:50,499 --> 00:21:53,179
I don't want to remember the past.

262
00:21:58,490 --> 00:22:00,970
And in the future, if I...

263
00:22:02,450 --> 00:22:04,600
If I'm with you,

264
00:22:05,630 --> 00:22:08,080
and feel even a tinge of happiness,

265
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:12,310
won't it be sad when I die?

266
00:22:14,630 --> 00:22:16,520
And you...

267
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:22,000
shouldn't get involved
with someone who's dying anyway.

268
00:22:25,970 --> 00:22:28,100
You should forget about me.

269
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:37,540
It'll only cause you pain.

270
00:22:43,730 --> 00:22:45,800
Six months left...

271
00:22:48,550 --> 00:22:49,890
Is that true?

272
00:22:59,171 --> 00:23:04,541
The chemotherapy and radiation treatment
started last week.

273
00:23:08,970 --> 00:23:13,970
Being out and about like this...

274
00:23:15,720 --> 00:23:17,350
won't last much longer.

275
00:23:22,860 --> 00:23:24,590
So I'm begging you.

276
00:23:26,460 --> 00:23:28,100
Please...

277
00:23:32,740 --> 00:23:34,460
forget about me.

278
00:23:45,445 --> 00:23:47,010
Are you really sure?

279
00:23:47,010 --> 00:23:50,810
Letting go of everything
you worked so desperately to obtain...

280
00:23:50,810 --> 00:23:53,665
Koharu might not want to remember.

281
00:23:53,665 --> 00:23:57,229
If you end up suffering alone
as you did with Haruto...

282
00:23:57,229 --> 00:23:59,633
Thank you for being in Koharu's life.
